# Audio Transcription

[![Open with Zeno](https://img.shields.io/badge/%20-Open_with_Zeno-612593.svg?labelColor=white&logo=data:image/svg%2bxml;base64,)](https://hub.zenoml.com/project/e7519c8a-3c07-45ce-90f4-3a5ba4660ab6/LLM%20Taxes%20Benchmark)

In this example, we'll upload the output of the taxeval project.
To generate outputs for your own models, go to the [original repo](https://github.com/danielgross/taxeval).

The result of running Zeno Build will be an interface where you
can browse and explore the results. See an example below:

- [Browsing Interface](https://hub.zenoml.com/project/e7519c8a-3c07-45ce-90f4-3a5ba4660ab6/LLM%20Taxes%20Benchmark)
- [Textual Summary](https://hub.zenoml.com/report/1717/Can%20LLMs%20do%20Your%20Taxes%3F)

## Setup

To run this example, you'll need to install the requirements.

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Run the Example

Follow `transcription.ipynb` to run inference and generate a Zeno project.
